        "answer": "B. \\frac{3\\sqrt{2}}{2}"
      }
    ],
    "veryShortAnswerQuestions": [
      {
        "question": "What is the conjugate of (4 + вҲҡ5)?",
        "answer": "(4 - вҲҡ5)"
      },
      {
        "question": "Simplify: 1/вҲҡ2 Г— вҲҡ2/вҲҡ2.",
        "answer": "\\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2}"
      }
    ],
    "didYouKnow": [
      "Ancient Greek mathematicians like Euclid worked with lengths rather than numbers, so they often avoided irrational denominators in their geometric proofs."
    ],
    "summary": [
      "Rationalizing the denominator is a standard algebraic technique to simplify expressions involving square roots."
    ],
    "quickRevision": [
      "Multiply by root/root for single terms; multiply by conjugate for binomials."
    ],
    "rememberPoints": [
      "вҲҡx Г— вҲҡx = x",
      "(a+b)(a-b) = aВІ - bВІ"
    ]
  }
}
